Lamu West MP Julius Ndegwa has said a political witchhunt has fuelled the legal suits he faces at the moment.Ndegwa is accused of misusing Sh6 million of CDF money for his constituency.Shortly after the 2013 election, the legislator had his victory challenged in the High Court by rival Rishad Amana.Ndegwa won the case and said his rivals were behind it all. Speaking in Mpeketoni on Tuesday, the MP said he is undeterred by the challenges he faces and is confident of retaining his seat.Ndegwa said despite the frustrations, he has still delivered his promises to Lamu West residents.Ndegwa said he is aware of a plot by his political rivals who want to use the court petitions to frustrate his candidature in next month&rsquo;s election.